Vice President Mike Pence visited Buenos Aires, Argentina, where he laid a wreath at General San Martin's tomb and visited a memorial for Holocaust victims. He met with Argentine President Mauricio Macri to discuss trade issues, Argentina's global leadership role, and the deteriorating situation in Venezuela. Pence also spoke to Argentine and Latin American business leaders about the region's progress in terms of prosperity and security. He ended his visit by meeting with embassy staff and their families to express gratitude for their work on behalf of the American people.